Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with 1/4 tsp @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the #pot{} and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet}, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Break it up as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Add the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Creme Fraiche{75%g}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Peas{120%g}, @Honey{1%tbsp}, @Water{75%ml} and a knob of @?butter{}. Stir to combine.

Bring to the boil and simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share the rice between #bowls{}.

Top with the Cajun beef.

Sprinkle over the @Crispy Onions{1%sachet}.

Enjoy!